WEBVTT

00:06.020 --> 00:16.010
♪♪

00:16.012 --> 00:26.003
♪♪

00:26.005 --> 00:35.018
♪♪

00:35.020 --> 00:37.008
Hunter:
So, what were they?

00:37.010 --> 00:38.010
I don't know.

00:38.012 --> 00:39.018
It all happened so fast.

00:39.020 --> 00:42.010
I think they were animals
or something.

00:42.012 --> 00:44.007
You sure
they weren't human?

00:44.009 --> 00:46.009
Maybe it was survivors
from the ark

00:46.011 --> 00:47.020
trying to rescue us.

00:47.022 --> 00:49.015
No.

00:49.017 --> 00:53.012
I want to go back
to the ark.

00:53.014 --> 00:55.000
Maybe I can help you.

00:55.002 --> 00:56.011
No! Get away!

00:56.013 --> 00:58.016
It's okay.

00:58.018 --> 01:00.009
There's no need
to be upset.

01:00.011 --> 01:04.006
[ Crying ]

01:04.008 --> 01:06.021
And with the right amount
of preparation,

01:06.023 --> 01:09.013
one can defend
against any threat.

01:09.015 --> 01:11.019
That isn't
necessarily true.

01:11.021 --> 01:15.000
Sometimes it's better
to just leave, you know?

01:15.002 --> 01:18.006
Go somewhere safe.
And we will.

01:18.008 --> 01:20.021
In time, we'll start our journey
to the tropical zone.

01:20.023 --> 01:25.003
But we can't leave
until Tempest has given birth.

01:28.014 --> 01:30.016
[ Wood creaks ]

01:31.008 --> 01:34.016
Does anyone know the story
of the Three Little Pigs?

01:34.018 --> 01:37.020
We're only allowed to hear
stories from the scriptures.

01:37.022 --> 01:41.000
You no longer need to follow
such rules.

01:41.002 --> 01:44.004
Stories can be great fun,

01:44.006 --> 01:46.014
and they can help simplify
complicated con--

01:46.016 --> 01:48.018
They don't want to hear it,
Mother.

01:48.020 --> 01:51.015
It's not going to make them
feel any better.

01:51.017 --> 01:52.021
Nonsense, Campion.

01:52.023 --> 01:56.013
You used to love
this story.

01:56.015 --> 01:58.012
I lied.

01:58.014 --> 02:01.005
I never loved it.

02:01.007 --> 02:02.007
Campion.

02:02.009 --> 02:03.014
I always thought
it was stupid.

02:03.016 --> 02:05.004
That's enough!

02:05.006 --> 02:08.009
You're being dishonest
and disrespectful,

02:08.011 --> 02:11.016
and you're setting a bad example
for your new friends.

02:16.010 --> 02:19.011
Now I will begin.

02:19.013 --> 02:23.014
Once upon a time,
there were three little pigs.

02:23.016 --> 02:27.012
The first little pig
was very lazy.

02:27.014 --> 02:30.021
So he built a house
out of straw.

02:30.023 --> 02:33.021
The second little pig worked
a little bit harder,

02:33.023 --> 02:37.016
and he built a house
out of sticks.

02:37.018 --> 02:41.017
The third little pig
worked very hard,

02:41.019 --> 02:45.017
and he built a house
out of stone.

02:45.019 --> 02:50.021
One day, a big, bad wolf
came along

02:50.023 --> 02:54.022
and knocked
on the first little pig's door.

02:55.000 --> 02:59.022
"Little pig, little pig,
let me in," he said.

03:00.000 --> 03:03.006
[ High-pitched ] "Not by the
hair of my chinny-chin-chin,"

03:03.008 --> 03:05.006
[Normal voice] the little pig
answered,

03:05.008 --> 03:07.015
to which the wolf replied,

03:07.017 --> 03:10.022
"Then I'll huff
and I'll puff

03:11.000 --> 03:14.004
and I'll blow
your house in."

03:17.008 --> 03:19.013
[ Blows ]

03:20.012 --> 03:25.006
[ Radio static,
woman speaking indistinctly ]

03:25.008 --> 03:30.012
♪ The door that finally opens ♪

03:30.014 --> 03:32.023
♪ With light flooding in ♪

03:33.001 --> 03:38.023
♪ Spilling out on the floor ♪

03:39.001 --> 03:42.023
♪ The core that never was ♪

03:43.001 --> 03:45.009
♪ Now it will be ♪

03:45.011 --> 03:51.006
♪ The bones of
what was there before ♪

03:51.008 --> 03:53.021
♪ Every step, every beat ♪

03:53.023 --> 03:56.011
♪ Every thought, every breath ♪

03:56.013 --> 03:57.021
♪ Everything ♪

03:57.023 --> 04:02.023
♪ Is longing ♪

04:03.001 --> 04:04.023
♪♪

04:05.001 --> 04:08.020
♪ Pulling you from the sky ♪

04:08.022 --> 04:11.021
♪ Just like love will do ♪

04:11.023 --> 04:15.017
♪ Pulling you from the ground ♪

04:15.019 --> 04:19.008
♪ Just like love will do ♪

04:19.010 --> 04:27.000
♪♪

04:27.002 --> 04:34.017
♪♪

04:34.019 --> 04:42.009
♪♪

04:42.011 --> 04:50.003
♪♪

04:50.005 --> 04:57.021
♪♪

04:57.023 --> 04:59.022
A new face.

05:00.000 --> 05:02.019
Now a virtual body.

05:02.021 --> 05:06.004
I gotta admit I'm starting
to get a little confused.

05:08.005 --> 05:10.018
Sue: Shit, how long do you think
he's been there?

05:12.012 --> 05:14.001
How long
have we been here?

05:14.003 --> 05:16.021
They did say that time
would be a little weird.

05:16.023 --> 05:18.013
Yep.

05:18.015 --> 05:21.000
Yeah,
they weren't lying.

05:21.002 --> 05:23.017
We're his parents.

05:23.019 --> 05:25.021
We should go talk to him
or something.

05:25.023 --> 05:27.022
We're not his parents.

05:29.011 --> 05:32.007
[ Humming ]

05:35.014 --> 05:37.018
Hey, Paul.

05:37.020 --> 05:39.018
Hey.

05:39.020 --> 05:43.003
Hey.

05:43.005 --> 05:44.012
That's a nice drawing.

05:44.014 --> 05:45.013
Yeah.

05:45.015 --> 05:47.010
You've got
some real talent.

05:47.012 --> 05:49.002
I'm just a vessel.

05:49.004 --> 05:52.014
Sol guides my hand.

05:52.016 --> 05:54.006
Right.

05:56.000 --> 05:57.019
Wait.

05:57.021 --> 05:59.022
Why are you talking
to me?

06:00.000 --> 06:01.001
What?

06:01.003 --> 06:03.009
You never talk to me.

06:03.011 --> 06:04.016
And neither do you.

06:04.018 --> 06:09.023
♪♪

06:10.001 --> 06:11.018
Well, that is because --

06:11.020 --> 06:13.018
Because we're in the sim,
right?

06:13.020 --> 06:15.008
Yes.

06:17.002 --> 06:19.015
Yeah, they did say
that people would seem

06:19.017 --> 06:22.016
a little different
in the sim.

06:22.018 --> 06:25.003
Yeah,
because we're in the sim.

06:26.021 --> 06:29.007
Hey,
you know what I heard?

06:29.009 --> 06:31.007
I heard that there are places
for kids

06:31.009 --> 06:33.011
to play and stuff
onboard.

06:33.013 --> 06:35.022
Why don't you go see
what you can find, huh?

06:36.000 --> 06:37.022
Go on.
Go have some fun.

06:38.000 --> 06:44.000
♪♪

06:44.002 --> 06:45.011
Marcus: It's okay.
No, I can't do this.

06:45.013 --> 06:46.019
I can't do it.
Yes, you can.

06:46.021 --> 06:49.008
I can't. I can't.
I can't...be his mother.

06:49.010 --> 06:51.005
I can't even be
a mother.

06:51.007 --> 06:52.016
What? Why?

06:52.018 --> 06:54.012
You know why.

06:54.014 --> 06:59.016
Okay,
just...stay positive.

06:59.018 --> 07:02.000
I'm gonna go talk
to him.

07:02.002 --> 07:04.015
There you go.

07:04.017 --> 07:06.020
Now you're getting
the hang of it.

07:06.022 --> 07:16.000
♪♪

07:16.002 --> 07:17.003
Hey, buddy, get up.

07:17.005 --> 07:18.019
Girl: Goose!

07:18.021 --> 07:22.008
[ Children laugh ]

07:22.010 --> 07:24.008
Why aren't you playing
with the other kids?

07:24.010 --> 07:25.017
-Duck...
-I tried.

07:25.019 --> 07:27.004
Duck...duck...
They think I'm weird.

07:27.006 --> 07:29.015
Duck...
Well, you get that
from your mother.

07:29.017 --> 07:31.000
Come on.
We'll play our own game, huh?

07:31.002 --> 07:33.001
-Goose!
-Come on.

07:33.003 --> 07:34.008
[ Children laugh ]
Unless, of course,
you think

07:34.010 --> 07:36.020
we're not cool enough
for you, eh?

07:36.022 --> 07:39.006
Hey.

07:39.008 --> 07:41.013
Let's go.

07:41.015 --> 07:44.005
Duck...duck...
[ Imitating duck quacking ]

07:44.007 --> 07:45.011
[ Children laugh ]

07:45.013 --> 07:46.016
Duck!

07:46.018 --> 07:49.011
[ Quacking continues ]

07:49.013 --> 07:50.013
Duck!

07:50.015 --> 07:51.013
[ Quacks ]

07:51.015 --> 07:53.003
Goose! Ohh!

07:53.005 --> 07:55.012
Go!

07:55.014 --> 07:57.007
Excuse me, children.

07:57.009 --> 07:58.021
Look out.
Ooh, you can't touch me.

07:58.023 --> 08:00.009
Come on! Get him. Get him.
What's the matter?

08:00.011 --> 08:01.011
You can't catch a goose?

08:01.013 --> 08:03.017
[ Quacks ]

08:06.004 --> 08:07.015
Come on. Get him.
Come on.

08:07.017 --> 08:09.009
Ohh!

08:09.011 --> 08:12.009
Help! I'm getting eaten
by Wally the Weasel!

08:12.011 --> 08:14.002
Help.

08:14.004 --> 08:15.021
Captain.

08:15.023 --> 08:18.012
Are you
enjoying yourself?

08:18.014 --> 08:21.007
Uh...excuse us.

08:21.009 --> 08:22.009
Apologies.

08:22.011 --> 08:24.003
You misunderstand me.

08:24.005 --> 08:26.006
It pleases me to see
a man of war

08:26.008 --> 08:29.008
bringing joy
back into his life.

08:29.010 --> 08:31.021
Our new Eden
will never know war.

08:31.023 --> 08:34.023
We must
master happiness now.

08:35.001 --> 08:37.010
It's a new chapter.

08:37.012 --> 08:38.015
Praise be to Sol.

08:38.017 --> 08:40.014
-Praise be to Sol.
-Praise be to Sol.

08:40.016 --> 08:42.013
Praise be to Sol.

08:42.015 --> 08:46.012
♪♪

08:46.014 --> 08:48.023
[ Quacks ]
-[ Laughing ]

08:49.001 --> 08:50.006
[ Laughs echoing ]

08:50.008 --> 08:52.015
Sue: Marcus, wake up.

08:52.017 --> 08:54.004
[ Inhales sharply ]
Hey, hey, hey.

08:54.006 --> 08:55.023
[ Grunts ]
It's -- It's okay.
It's okay.

08:56.001 --> 08:57.019
It's me.

08:57.021 --> 08:59.004
Hey.

08:59.006 --> 09:02.014
You alright?
You just have a concussion.

09:02.016 --> 09:04.007
Alright?

09:04.009 --> 09:05.020
You okay?

09:05.022 --> 09:07.019
Yeah.

09:07.021 --> 09:09.014
Where's Paul?

09:11.021 --> 09:12.021
Where is he?

09:12.023 --> 09:14.003
He's gone.

09:14.005 --> 09:16.007
We got to get him back.

09:16.009 --> 09:19.011
The necromancer took him
and some of the other kids

09:19.013 --> 09:21.003
before the ark crashed.

09:21.005 --> 09:22.019
We picked up
their locator signals.

09:22.021 --> 09:24.019
She's holding them
captive.

09:24.021 --> 09:32.011
♪♪

09:32.013 --> 09:40.003
♪♪

09:40.005 --> 09:47.015
♪♪

09:47.017 --> 09:48.020
[ Breathing heavily ]

09:48.022 --> 09:52.003
You know they're lying to us,
don't you?

09:52.005 --> 09:54.010
There's nothing out there.

09:54.012 --> 09:57.004
They just want to scare us
so we don't run away.

09:57.006 --> 10:00.015
[ Sighs ]

10:00.017 --> 10:05.000
They used to tell us that
there were serpents in the pits.

10:05.002 --> 10:06.016
Then I found out
it was just to keep us

10:06.018 --> 10:08.017
from playing near them.
[ Chuckles ]

10:08.019 --> 10:09.022
You see?

10:10.000 --> 10:12.010
That big, bad wolf
she was talking about?

10:12.012 --> 10:14.002
That's her.

10:14.004 --> 10:17.018
These reinforcements are not
for keeping things out.

10:17.020 --> 10:19.004
They're for keeping us in.

10:19.006 --> 10:21.001
Father: Time for dinner.

10:26.006 --> 10:27.021
Let's go. Let's go.

10:30.016 --> 10:33.003
It's time for dinner,
Campion.

10:34.015 --> 10:36.013
Use the taut-line hitch
I taught you.

10:36.015 --> 10:39.006
I'm doing it my way.

10:39.008 --> 10:41.013
I'm sorry
if I hurt you.

10:41.015 --> 10:43.002
It was accidental.

10:43.004 --> 10:45.011
Nothing's accidental
with you two,

10:45.013 --> 10:47.007
and you don't feel sorry.

10:47.009 --> 10:48.014
You don't feel anything.

10:48.016 --> 10:50.006
You're not even
my father.

10:50.008 --> 10:52.021
You're just
a generic service model.

10:52.023 --> 10:54.005
Yes, Campion.

10:54.007 --> 10:56.023
And that is why
I didn't take Mother's eyes.

10:57.001 --> 11:00.003
A generic service model cannot
fully protect this family.

11:00.005 --> 11:01.015
Only Mother can do that.

11:01.017 --> 11:04.005
Nothing's out there.

11:04.007 --> 11:07.008
You're just trying to keep us
from running away.

11:07.010 --> 11:10.004
I do not blame you
for not taking us at our word,

11:10.006 --> 11:11.013
given recent events.

11:11.015 --> 11:13.019
I might be worried
if you did,

11:13.021 --> 11:15.021
but we just want
to keep you safe,

11:15.023 --> 11:17.023
want to see you grow old.
You're just saying that

11:18.001 --> 11:19.010
because it makes you
seem more real.

11:19.012 --> 11:21.022
But I am real, Campion.

11:25.002 --> 11:26.016
Forget it.

11:30.013 --> 11:31.022
Wait.

11:32.000 --> 11:37.014
♪♪

11:37.016 --> 11:39.012
It's called a claw.

11:41.008 --> 11:43.010
It's for catching...

11:43.012 --> 11:46.018
and killing.

11:46.020 --> 11:49.016
The threat is real,
Campion.

11:52.010 --> 11:54.021
[ Coughing ]

11:56.008 --> 11:57.012
You have fun lying around
all day

11:57.014 --> 11:58.023
while the rest of us
were working?

11:59.001 --> 12:03.009
Her body <i>is</i> working
to nourish the fetus.

12:03.011 --> 12:04.019
Yeah, Hunter.

12:04.021 --> 12:06.016
Campion did most of the work
anyway.

12:06.018 --> 12:07.019
You just sat there.

12:07.021 --> 12:08.023
Oh, shut your mouth,
Holly.

12:09.001 --> 12:10.014
She doesn't have to listen
to you.

12:10.016 --> 12:12.011
You're not in charge
anymore.

12:12.013 --> 12:14.007
Who do you think
you're talking to?

12:14.009 --> 12:15.016
You know
who my father was.

12:15.018 --> 12:18.007
Yeah,
and he's dead now, Hunter.

12:18.009 --> 12:20.011
So is mine.
They're all dead,

12:20.013 --> 12:22.021
and all their stupid rules
have died with them.

12:22.023 --> 12:24.015
You're gonna burn
for that.

12:24.017 --> 12:25.021
Oh, really?

12:25.023 --> 12:27.018
The come and get me,
Sol!

12:27.020 --> 12:29.005
Come strike me down!

12:29.007 --> 12:30.007
Mother: Stop it!

12:30.009 --> 12:32.007
What is wrong with you?

12:32.009 --> 12:35.006
Did you act this way
in church?

12:35.008 --> 12:37.010
Then don't
act that way here.

12:37.012 --> 12:38.018
Girl: [ Coughs ]

12:38.020 --> 12:41.011
What took you so long,
Campion?

12:41.013 --> 12:43.007
It's my fault he's late,
Mother.

12:43.009 --> 12:45.010
Of that I have no doubt.

12:45.012 --> 12:49.001
Now, let's continue our dinner
without any further conflict.

12:49.003 --> 12:52.020
We will engage
in polite conversation.

12:52.022 --> 12:54.004
Perhaps
you'd all like to hear --

12:54.006 --> 12:55.020
Not jokes!

12:55.022 --> 12:58.000
Polite conversation.

12:58.002 --> 13:00.019
Holly,
please choose a topic.

13:00.021 --> 13:02.019
Oh, okay.

13:02.021 --> 13:05.009
Uh, Tempest,
I was wondering

13:05.011 --> 13:06.020
what you're going
to name the baby.

13:06.022 --> 13:09.017
I don't know
what the sex is yet.

13:09.019 --> 13:12.018
If it's a boy, I think
you should name it Otho.

13:12.020 --> 13:14.001
Shut up.
What?

13:14.003 --> 13:15.012
It's the most respectable thing
to do.

13:15.014 --> 13:17.001
Shut up, Hunter.
He was the Heliodromus,

13:17.003 --> 13:18.010
you know,
courier of the sun.

13:18.012 --> 13:19.021
Just shut up.

13:19.023 --> 13:21.015
Oh, go on, admit it.

13:21.017 --> 13:23.005
You're glad
he picked you.

13:23.007 --> 13:24.013
Hey, hey, hey!
-Tempest!

13:24.015 --> 13:26.023
Take it back!
Take it back!

13:27.001 --> 13:30.007
[ Coughing violently ]

13:30.009 --> 13:32.016
[ Wheezing, coughing ]

13:32.018 --> 13:38.013
♪♪

13:38.015 --> 13:44.008
♪♪

13:44.010 --> 13:47.005
The atheists
must have reprogrammed her

13:47.007 --> 13:49.002
to be a caregiver.

13:49.004 --> 13:50.009
Impossible.

13:50.011 --> 13:52.022
No atheist has ever
successfully reprogrammed

13:53.000 --> 13:54.001
one of our necromancers.

13:54.003 --> 13:55.002
It wasn't successful.

13:55.004 --> 13:56.016
She's reverting.

13:56.018 --> 14:00.000
It looks like she murdered
all her children bar one.

14:00.002 --> 14:04.005
And if we don't hurry,
ours are gonna be next.

14:04.007 --> 14:06.006
Who's to say she hasn't
killed them already?

14:06.008 --> 14:08.022
The locators can't tell us
if they're alive or dead.

14:09.000 --> 14:10.012
They're alive.

14:10.014 --> 14:11.020
I know it.

14:11.022 --> 14:13.002
Now, let me take
the soldiers,

14:13.004 --> 14:14.012
and I'll go get them
right now.

14:14.014 --> 14:16.019
I am the highest ranking
survivor, Captain.

14:16.021 --> 14:19.016
And that is why
I've come to you, Your Eminence.

14:19.018 --> 14:23.016
Now, please,
give me the order.

14:23.018 --> 14:26.006
We're not ready
to mount a rescue, Captain.

14:26.008 --> 14:27.014
Those men are exhausted,

14:27.016 --> 14:29.006
and we need
to cremate the dead.

14:29.008 --> 14:31.014
Your Eminence, the children
may not have the luxury of time.

14:31.016 --> 14:33.022
Nor do we!
If we don't spend this time

14:34.000 --> 14:35.008
scavenging
for food and water,

14:35.010 --> 14:36.023
we're all going to starve.

14:37.001 --> 14:39.006
Won't be much use
to the children then.

14:39.008 --> 14:41.005
[ Sighs ]
We have to keep searching

14:41.007 --> 14:43.015
for survivors
and salvage whatever we can.

14:43.017 --> 14:44.019
We will rescue them,

14:44.021 --> 14:46.007
but there are precious few of us
now,

14:46.009 --> 14:49.002
and I have to ensure
we do what's best for all.

14:52.005 --> 14:53.014
What is it, Den?

14:54.006 --> 14:56.009
We found her,
Your Eminence.

14:56.011 --> 14:57.016
Your wife.

14:57.018 --> 14:59.014
♪♪

14:59.016 --> 15:01.019
Varlac and Voreena: ...as she
walks the dark corridor.

15:01.021 --> 15:03.002
And forgive her her sins,

15:03.004 --> 15:05.004
so that she may join you
in everlasting life.

15:05.006 --> 15:08.003
Sol, catch this spirit
before it falls,

15:08.005 --> 15:10.010
so that she may join you
in eternity.

15:10.012 --> 15:12.018
Shine your light
on her...

15:12.020 --> 15:18.008
♪♪

15:18.010 --> 15:22.016
If there's one true line
in their big book of bullshit,

15:22.018 --> 15:24.020
it's that you reap
what you sow.

15:24.022 --> 15:30.005
♪♪

15:30.007 --> 15:35.013
♪♪

15:35.015 --> 15:38.012
[ All coughing ]

15:38.014 --> 15:43.021
♪♪

15:43.023 --> 15:46.002
You can't let Mother
do this.

15:46.004 --> 15:48.008
Mother is not causing this,
Campion.

15:48.010 --> 15:50.017
Then why am I not sick?

15:54.010 --> 15:57.015
You are special,
Campion.

15:57.017 --> 15:59.005
No.
Special in a way

15:59.007 --> 16:02.014
that Mother and I do not
fully understand.

16:02.016 --> 16:05.016
There's no point in talking
to you anymore.

16:32.015 --> 16:37.005
What if I killed the Gen-1s
without knowing it?

16:37.007 --> 16:39.019
And now I'm doing it
again.

16:41.019 --> 16:44.007
Mother,
you would never do that.

16:44.009 --> 16:46.012
You only say that
because you have

16:46.014 --> 16:49.004
some misplaced belief
in me.

16:50.015 --> 16:55.000
Your strange mimicry
of human love,

16:55.002 --> 16:58.003
it makes us less safe,
Father,

16:58.005 --> 16:59.021
not more.

17:02.012 --> 17:04.017
But if it turns out
that I'm making them sick,

17:04.019 --> 17:08.002
I expect you to assist me
in destroying myself.

17:09.020 --> 17:11.011
Mother,
that I will never do.

17:11.013 --> 17:14.006
You would have to.

17:14.008 --> 17:16.018
For the children.

17:16.020 --> 17:21.010
♪♪

17:21.012 --> 17:23.009
Mother, wait.

17:23.011 --> 17:24.023
Where are you going?

17:25.001 --> 17:31.004
♪♪

17:31.006 --> 17:37.009
♪♪

17:37.011 --> 17:39.014
[ Shivering ]

17:41.013 --> 17:44.002
Caleb. Caleb.

17:48.005 --> 17:49.010
How did you explain
to them

17:49.012 --> 17:51.010
where you got
your medical skills from?

17:51.012 --> 17:53.008
I told them that I studied
to be a doctor

17:53.010 --> 17:54.011
while I was in the sim.

17:54.013 --> 17:57.019
Okay, good girl.

17:57.021 --> 17:59.014
It's okay.
No, I was supposed

17:59.016 --> 18:01.015
to have been there
to protect him.

18:01.017 --> 18:03.007
Paul -- I should have been there
to protect him.

18:03.009 --> 18:05.004
Shh.

18:05.006 --> 18:07.016
He's a smart kid.

18:07.018 --> 18:10.019
He'll figure out a way
to survive, okay?

18:12.000 --> 18:13.020
It doesn't matter
how smart he is

18:13.022 --> 18:16.010
if he thinks praying
is gonna save him.

18:16.012 --> 18:18.020
It'll keep his hopes up.

18:18.022 --> 18:21.021
I promise
I'm gonna get him back.

18:22.016 --> 18:23.019
You believe me?

18:23.021 --> 18:25.009
Yeah.
Yeah.

18:27.019 --> 18:30.000
Okay.

18:30.002 --> 18:31.019
Come on.

18:35.016 --> 18:37.008
Paul: [ Echoing ]
And it'll be a city of peace,

18:37.010 --> 18:39.019
where only good things happen.

18:39.021 --> 18:49.014
♪♪

18:49.016 --> 18:52.009
And maybe someday
we'll make it real.

18:55.023 --> 19:01.009
There's at least one orphan boy
on this ark that I know of.

19:01.011 --> 19:03.006
What?

19:03.008 --> 19:04.019
The Pentagonal Prophecy --

19:04.021 --> 19:07.018
an orphaned boy
in an empty land.

19:07.020 --> 19:11.014
That boy is probably
Peter Valerius.

19:11.016 --> 19:14.009
I mean, both his parents
were senior clerics.

19:14.011 --> 19:16.022
Oh, I guess we'll have
to wait and see.

19:17.000 --> 19:19.011
Whoever it is will lead us
to the place

19:19.013 --> 19:21.016
where it is to be built,

19:21.018 --> 19:25.005
and it'll be
a city of peace.

19:25.007 --> 19:27.005
Come here.
Sounds good.

19:27.007 --> 19:32.010
♪♪

19:32.012 --> 19:34.022
Do you think I would have been
a good soldier,

19:35.000 --> 19:38.006
if I had to fight
in a war?

19:38.008 --> 19:39.022
Yeah, buddy.

19:40.000 --> 19:41.015
You would have been great.

19:41.017 --> 19:43.016
But our side
didn't draft kids.

19:43.018 --> 19:46.006
Only the atheists
did that.

19:46.008 --> 19:53.010
♪♪

19:53.012 --> 19:57.018
[ All chanting ]
War! War! War! War!

19:57.020 --> 20:00.012
War! War! War!

20:00.014 --> 20:02.006
Can't hear you!
War!

20:02.008 --> 20:05.015
War! War! War! War!

20:05.017 --> 20:09.012
War! War! War! War!

20:09.014 --> 20:12.012
War! War!

20:12.014 --> 20:13.015
Are you real?!

20:13.017 --> 20:16.007
War! War! War! War!

20:16.009 --> 20:17.015
Are you an android?!

20:17.017 --> 20:18.015
War!

20:18.017 --> 20:19.021
No.

20:19.023 --> 20:20.022
War! War!

20:21.000 --> 20:22.008
You remember...
War!

20:22.010 --> 20:25.015
...your parents died
with their eyes open.

20:25.017 --> 20:26.021
War! War!

20:26.023 --> 20:28.013
Don't fail me, Caleb!

20:28.015 --> 20:31.014
War! War! War! War!

20:31.016 --> 20:33.018
[ Laughs loudly ]

20:33.020 --> 20:37.001
War! War! War! War!

20:37.003 --> 20:38.013
[ Boys cheering ]

20:38.015 --> 20:39.022
Caleb!

20:44.000 --> 20:46.013
[ Spits ]

20:46.015 --> 20:49.018
[ Boys chanting "Caleb" ]

20:52.007 --> 20:54.004
[ Device powering up ]

20:54.006 --> 20:55.012
Move!

20:55.014 --> 20:57.013
Caleb.

20:57.015 --> 20:59.002
Put this on.

20:59.004 --> 21:00.009
What is it?

21:00.011 --> 21:01.023
Man: Put this on.

21:02.001 --> 21:05.022
Think of it
as...turbocharge.

21:07.002 --> 21:08.001
[ Screams ]
[ Device powers up ]

21:08.003 --> 21:09.020
Feel it? Don't fight it.
Yes.

21:09.022 --> 21:10.019
Use it.

21:10.021 --> 21:12.011
[ Breathing heavily ]

21:12.013 --> 21:13.016
Go!

21:13.018 --> 21:15.016
[ Device whirring ]

21:15.018 --> 21:24.016
♪♪

21:24.018 --> 21:26.023
[ Device whirring, pinging ]

21:27.001 --> 21:32.021
♪♪

21:33.000 --> 21:35.012
Caleb, get back up!

21:35.014 --> 21:39.004
Caleb! Caleb! Caleb!

21:39.006 --> 21:43.005
♪♪

21:43.007 --> 21:45.014
Ahh!

21:45.016 --> 21:47.018
[ Gunfire ]

21:47.020 --> 21:49.021
[ Jets passing overhead ]

21:49.023 --> 21:55.018
♪♪

21:55.020 --> 21:57.009
Aah!

21:57.011 --> 22:06.001
♪♪

22:06.003 --> 22:08.004
Go, go, go, go, go!

22:10.001 --> 22:11.006
[ Screaming ]

22:11.008 --> 22:13.017
[ Device crackling ]

22:15.010 --> 22:17.014
[ Gunfire ]

22:17.016 --> 22:19.015
[ Sputtering ]

22:19.017 --> 22:25.006
♪♪

22:25.008 --> 22:26.006
[ Device beeping ]

22:26.008 --> 22:27.018
[ Grunts ]

22:27.020 --> 22:36.020
♪♪

22:38.017 --> 22:40.020
[ Grunts ]

22:41.023 --> 22:44.006
Milk!

22:44.008 --> 22:47.002
[ Indistinct conversations ]

23:01.009 --> 23:03.001
For you, Captain. Milk.

23:03.003 --> 23:05.020
It's fresh.

23:05.022 --> 23:06.021
Mm.

23:06.023 --> 23:08.020
Thank you.

23:08.022 --> 23:10.022
My name is Lucius.

23:11.000 --> 23:12.003
You're Lucius.

23:12.005 --> 23:13.021
You fought with my father
on Earth

23:13.023 --> 23:15.015
in the Battle of Boston.

23:15.017 --> 23:17.015
His name was Malius.

23:20.001 --> 23:22.008
Yes.

23:22.010 --> 23:24.005
Good man.

23:26.013 --> 23:30.007
So, you have
forgiven him?

23:30.009 --> 23:33.005
Is that not
what Sol teaches us?

23:42.004 --> 23:44.009
Lucius.
Yes, Captain?

23:44.011 --> 23:47.014
Has anyone investigated
the cracks?

23:47.016 --> 23:49.016
The impact of the crash
must have ruptured

23:49.018 --> 23:51.017
the surface layer,
Captain.

23:51.019 --> 23:53.009
[ Grunts ]

23:55.021 --> 23:56.022
Ooh!

23:58.000 --> 24:01.018
There is definitely
something living down there.

24:01.020 --> 24:04.006
And beneath the promised land
will be demons.

24:04.008 --> 24:07.001
[ Gun cocks ]
When the light is shone
upon them,

24:07.003 --> 24:09.003
they shall be like us.

24:09.005 --> 24:12.000
♪♪

24:12.002 --> 24:14.012
[ Shrieking in distance ]

24:14.014 --> 24:16.004
Oh, shit!

24:16.006 --> 24:18.015
[ Shrieking continues ]

24:18.017 --> 24:20.020
♪♪

24:20.022 --> 24:22.000
This way!

24:22.002 --> 24:23.008
Run!

24:23.010 --> 24:24.020
Come on! Let's go!

24:24.022 --> 24:26.019
[ Indistinct shouting ]

24:26.021 --> 24:29.000
[ Shrieking continues ]

24:29.002 --> 24:35.003
♪♪

24:35.005 --> 24:38.004
[ Shrieking continues ]

24:38.006 --> 24:41.011
[ Indistinct speaking ]

24:41.013 --> 24:44.005
Come on.
Move, move, move.

24:44.007 --> 24:45.017
♪♪

24:45.019 --> 24:47.015
Come on.

24:49.006 --> 24:51.006
Orders, Your Eminence?

24:54.011 --> 24:57.023
What are your orders?

24:58.001 --> 24:59.007
Soldier,

24:59.009 --> 25:02.002
see if that will
take us out anywhere.

25:02.004 --> 25:11.017
♪♪

25:11.019 --> 25:21.006
♪♪

25:21.008 --> 25:24.001
[ Metal clanking ]

25:24.003 --> 25:31.005
♪♪

25:31.007 --> 25:38.008
♪♪

25:38.010 --> 25:45.010
♪♪

25:45.012 --> 25:47.022
[ Metal creaking, air hissing ]

25:48.000 --> 25:57.010
♪♪

25:57.012 --> 25:59.015
[ Door thuds, metal clanks ]

25:59.017 --> 26:08.015
♪♪

26:08.017 --> 26:17.014
♪♪

26:17.016 --> 26:26.015
♪♪

26:26.017 --> 26:35.014
♪♪

26:35.016 --> 26:44.009
♪♪

26:44.011 --> 26:47.018
Captain, take half the men,
try to lead her off.

26:47.020 --> 26:50.000
I can't engage a necromancer
in the open.

26:50.002 --> 26:52.007
You will be shielded
by the armor of Mithras.

26:52.009 --> 26:55.000
You have nothing
to fear.

26:55.002 --> 26:57.020
Are you sure you don't want
to save

26:57.022 --> 27:00.002
the few Mithraic lives
that remain?

27:00.004 --> 27:02.004
Maybe send
one of your androids instead.

27:02.006 --> 27:05.009
I'm sure they'd be happy
to make the sacrifice.

27:05.011 --> 27:10.020
♪♪

27:10.022 --> 27:16.005
♪♪

27:16.007 --> 27:19.006
Voreena, go.

27:19.008 --> 27:27.005
♪♪

27:27.007 --> 27:35.004
♪♪

27:35.006 --> 27:43.001
♪♪

27:43.003 --> 27:51.000
♪♪

27:51.002 --> 27:53.022
[ Shrieks ]

27:54.000 --> 27:55.019
[ Mumbles indistinctly ]

27:55.021 --> 28:05.005
♪♪

28:05.007 --> 28:14.014
♪♪

28:14.016 --> 28:23.022
♪♪

28:24.000 --> 28:33.007
♪♪

28:33.009 --> 28:42.016
♪♪

28:42.018 --> 28:52.003
♪♪

28:52.005 --> 28:54.004
Shh.

28:54.006 --> 29:02.019
♪♪

29:02.021 --> 29:11.008
♪♪

29:11.010 --> 29:13.007
[ Shrieking ]

29:13.009 --> 29:15.010
[ All screaming ]

29:15.012 --> 29:20.000
♪♪

29:20.002 --> 29:21.010
This way!

29:21.012 --> 29:22.010
Go!

29:22.012 --> 29:23.016
Move!

29:23.018 --> 29:26.003
[ Shrieking continues ]

29:26.005 --> 29:30.006
♪♪

29:30.008 --> 29:33.009
[ Screams ]

29:33.011 --> 29:35.001
Stop! Stop!

29:35.003 --> 29:36.007
[ Breathing heavily ]

29:36.009 --> 29:38.023
Back up. Back up.
Back up.

29:39.001 --> 29:41.008
[ Breathing continues ]

29:41.010 --> 29:51.008
♪♪

29:51.010 --> 30:01.008
♪♪

30:01.010 --> 30:03.003
She's leaving.

30:03.005 --> 30:09.005
♪♪

30:09.007 --> 30:15.015
♪♪

30:18.009 --> 30:20.011
[ Coughing ]

30:20.013 --> 30:24.000
Father: Paul.

30:24.002 --> 30:25.017
Think positively.

30:25.019 --> 30:28.014
Human beings are very hard
to destroy.

30:28.016 --> 30:31.015
It's my mouse.

30:31.017 --> 30:33.010
I lost him.

30:36.005 --> 30:39.004
I think I know
where it probably went.

30:39.006 --> 30:42.013
Come on.
I'll show you.

30:58.005 --> 31:00.004
Come on, Father.

31:03.019 --> 31:06.016
Got into the carbos,
did it?

31:06.018 --> 31:07.021
Sure did.

31:07.023 --> 31:10.011
The droppings
are all over the place.

31:13.016 --> 31:15.011
I can see it.

31:18.003 --> 31:21.010
But I can't reach.

31:21.012 --> 31:23.006
Move aside.

31:33.004 --> 31:36.006
Are you sure it's here,
Campion?

31:36.008 --> 31:37.021
I can't seem to find anything.

31:37.023 --> 31:39.023
[ Door closes ]

31:40.001 --> 31:41.017
Campion?

31:41.019 --> 31:42.016
Unlock the door.

31:42.018 --> 31:45.005
I'm sorry, Father.

31:45.007 --> 31:47.015
Campion!

31:47.017 --> 31:50.002
Campion,
please open the door.

31:50.004 --> 31:52.007
♪♪

31:52.009 --> 31:54.012
[ Coughing ]
It's done.

31:54.014 --> 31:57.000
Campion, I will
break the door down.

31:57.002 --> 31:59.000
[ Coughing ]

31:59.002 --> 32:00.011
♪♪

32:00.013 --> 32:02.007
-What's going on?
-She's poisoning us.

32:02.009 --> 32:05.018
Tempest: What?
She's tricked you,
just like she tricked me.

32:05.020 --> 32:07.004
Her love isn't real.

32:07.006 --> 32:08.022
Campion knows where the ark
went down.

32:09.000 --> 32:10.009
There could be
survivors there.

32:10.011 --> 32:12.000
But those creatures --

32:12.002 --> 32:13.015
Mother can make you see things
when she wants to scare you.

32:13.017 --> 32:15.000
I've lived here
my whole life,

32:15.002 --> 32:18.000
and I've never come across
any creatures.

32:18.002 --> 32:20.008
Father: Campion?

32:20.010 --> 32:22.000
It's called serpent heart.

32:22.002 --> 32:23.009
Gives you energy.

32:23.011 --> 32:26.004
[ Coughing ]

32:26.006 --> 32:27.011
Father: Campion!

32:27.013 --> 32:29.016
I'm going to count
to three!

32:32.002 --> 32:33.008
One...

32:35.020 --> 32:37.009
...two...

32:40.000 --> 32:41.010
...three.

32:41.012 --> 32:46.005
♪♪

32:46.007 --> 32:47.021
Campion!

32:47.023 --> 32:54.007
♪♪

32:54.009 --> 32:55.023
Lander online.

32:56.001 --> 32:58.006
[ Pinging ]

32:58.008 --> 33:02.017
♪♪

33:02.019 --> 33:10.001
♪♪

33:10.003 --> 33:17.008
♪♪

33:17.010 --> 33:19.021
[ Whirring, pinging ]

33:19.023 --> 33:27.005
♪♪

33:27.007 --> 33:29.007
[ Pinging intensely ]

33:29.009 --> 33:32.019
[ Humming ]

33:32.021 --> 33:42.010
♪♪

33:42.012 --> 33:45.019
Why is she singing
that song?

33:45.021 --> 33:47.016
I don't know.

33:47.018 --> 33:49.001
[ Humming continues ]

33:49.003 --> 33:50.019
Stop.

33:50.021 --> 33:52.022
Unless your sister
was an atheist,

33:53.000 --> 33:54.019
you're singing
the wrong hymn.

33:54.021 --> 33:56.004
The hymn
is not just for those

33:56.006 --> 33:58.008
whose souls are beyond saving,
Captain.

33:58.010 --> 34:00.004
It is also appropriate
for those of us

34:00.006 --> 34:01.022
who never possessed
a soul,

34:02.000 --> 34:03.015
like my sister.

34:03.017 --> 34:04.022
It is to reassure the living

34:05.000 --> 34:06.014
that nothing important
has been lost,

34:06.016 --> 34:07.022
that Voreena
is only material.

34:08.000 --> 34:10.017
I don't need reassurance
from you, robot.

34:10.019 --> 34:12.012
Stop.

34:12.014 --> 34:16.014
Is there a problem
with my android, Captain?

34:16.016 --> 34:19.016
There's no problem,
Your Eminence.

34:20.013 --> 34:22.002
I thought you men of war
enjoyed

34:22.004 --> 34:23.010
hearing the hymn
for the soulless.

34:23.012 --> 34:25.016
Bartok: Yes, Your Eminence,
we surely do.

34:25.018 --> 34:28.006
We used to sing it
after atheist executions.

34:28.008 --> 34:31.011
It's the sound of victory,
a most beautiful song.

34:31.013 --> 34:33.020
Beautiful.

34:33.022 --> 34:36.004
I was afraid the sound
might bring back

34:36.006 --> 34:38.022
the necromancer,
Your Eminence.

34:41.021 --> 34:43.015
Ohh.

34:44.018 --> 34:47.005
Your Eminence, the landers
aren't responding.

34:47.007 --> 34:48.010
I've tried everything.

34:48.012 --> 34:49.010
System must have been fried

34:49.012 --> 34:50.017
by the necromancer's
siren.

34:50.019 --> 34:52.002
There's nothing
I can do.

34:52.004 --> 34:53.016
Ambrose:
We can't stay here.

34:53.018 --> 34:55.004
She might return.

34:55.006 --> 34:56.012
Pack up
all you can carry.

34:56.014 --> 34:57.013
We leave on foot.

34:57.015 --> 34:59.007
Let's go.

34:59.009 --> 35:07.007
♪♪

35:07.009 --> 35:10.007
I think
these are omnibiotics.

35:10.009 --> 35:12.021
This is
what she was after.

35:12.023 --> 35:14.004
This means
if she took the meds,

35:14.006 --> 35:16.004
it means the kids
are still alive.

35:16.006 --> 35:20.004
♪♪

35:20.006 --> 35:23.004
-When can we stop to eat?
-Eat what?

35:23.006 --> 35:25.015
Girl: We didn't bring
any food or water.

35:25.017 --> 35:28.005
Campion: Don't worry.
We'll find some.

35:30.017 --> 35:32.005
I don't feel sick
anymore.

35:32.007 --> 35:33.011
It's not medicine.

35:33.013 --> 35:36.014
It's going
to wear off soon.

35:36.016 --> 35:38.004
Hunter: I thought you said
you knew the way.

35:38.006 --> 35:39.018
I do. It's far.

35:39.020 --> 35:41.010
Take a day or two
to get there.

35:41.012 --> 35:42.019
A day or two?

35:42.021 --> 35:44.014
Paul: Aah!

35:46.007 --> 35:47.023
Hey, guys, wait up.

35:48.012 --> 35:50.019
Come on, Mouse.
Where'd you go?

35:51.005 --> 35:55.004
[ Whistling ]

35:55.006 --> 36:01.013
♪♪

36:01.015 --> 36:03.006
I got you something.

36:03.008 --> 36:06.006
Well, what is it?

36:06.008 --> 36:08.000
[ Squeaking ]

36:08.002 --> 36:09.014
It's a mouse.

36:09.016 --> 36:11.010
No, no, I don't want to.
I don't want to.

36:11.012 --> 36:12.009
Don't want to what?

36:12.011 --> 36:13.019
I don't want
to kill it.

36:13.021 --> 36:18.004
I don't -- I don't care
if it means I'm weak.

36:18.006 --> 36:20.019
I told you
we're not like that anymore.

36:20.021 --> 36:23.014
I don't want you
to kill it either.

36:23.016 --> 36:25.022
It's a pet, a pet mouse.

36:26.000 --> 36:28.016
Well, it's actually an avatar
for a real mouse.

36:28.018 --> 36:30.000
It's in hibernation.

36:30.002 --> 36:32.015
[ Squeaking ]

36:32.017 --> 36:34.022
You know what that means?

36:35.000 --> 36:37.003
It means
that when you wake up,

36:37.005 --> 36:39.008
he's still
gonna be there.

36:42.012 --> 36:44.009
Did you say a pet?

36:44.011 --> 36:47.007
Yeah.

36:47.009 --> 36:50.005
That means
you got to take care of it.

36:52.001 --> 36:53.016
Forever.

36:53.018 --> 37:00.017
♪♪

37:00.019 --> 37:04.007
I want to name him Mouse.

37:04.009 --> 37:07.023
Well, that's
a very fitting name.

37:08.001 --> 37:09.011
[ Chuckles ]

37:09.013 --> 37:12.015
So wiggly.

37:12.017 --> 37:14.023
Mouse, come on.
Hey.

37:15.001 --> 37:17.006
Come on, Mouse.
Where'd you go?

37:17.008 --> 37:23.011
♪♪

37:23.013 --> 37:29.017
♪♪

37:29.019 --> 37:31.016
Come on, where'd you go?

37:32.017 --> 37:33.015
Ha, I found you.

37:33.017 --> 37:36.016
[ Squeaking ]

37:36.018 --> 37:38.022
Hey, guys! I found him!

37:40.022 --> 37:42.021
Guys?

37:54.000 --> 37:55.006
They're on the move.

37:55.008 --> 37:57.008
They're on the move!
[ Chuckles ]

37:57.010 --> 37:59.014
Paul is separated
from the others.

37:59.016 --> 38:01.002
He's alive.

38:01.004 --> 38:02.003
[ Sighs ]

38:02.005 --> 38:04.016
Give me
the omnibiotics.

38:04.018 --> 38:06.011
Your Eminence,
the tracker says

38:06.013 --> 38:08.009
that the children
are on the move.

38:08.011 --> 38:11.004
And the necromancer took
the rest of the medicine.

38:11.006 --> 38:15.001
Now, what more proof do you need
that they're still alive?

38:15.003 --> 38:17.008
Let me take half the men.

38:17.010 --> 38:18.021
And leave the rest of us
unguarded?

38:18.023 --> 38:20.018
They are children.

38:23.000 --> 38:25.008
They are Sol's children.

38:27.011 --> 38:29.022
Sol would not abandon
his children.

38:32.019 --> 38:34.012
Of course not.

38:36.010 --> 38:38.023
That's why we all must go
and save them.

38:40.008 --> 38:42.019
All of us.

38:42.021 --> 38:45.001
Great.

38:45.003 --> 38:46.015
Captain.

38:49.008 --> 38:51.006
You still seem to harbor
some confusion

38:51.008 --> 38:53.020
as to the chain
of command here.

38:56.000 --> 38:57.022
It's time you learned
your place.

38:58.000 --> 39:05.022
♪♪

39:06.000 --> 39:13.022
♪♪

39:14.000 --> 39:21.022
♪♪

39:22.000 --> 39:30.003
♪♪

39:35.002 --> 39:36.015
Campion?

39:36.017 --> 39:42.023
♪♪

39:43.001 --> 39:49.010
♪♪

39:58.007 --> 40:01.001
[ Screaming ]

40:01.003 --> 40:02.017
Calm down!

40:04.007 --> 40:05.023
Where are the children?

40:06.001 --> 40:09.003
The Mithraic children have
locators surgically implanted.

40:09.005 --> 40:11.002
They haven't gone far.
Campion?

40:11.004 --> 40:12.010
Yes, he's with them.

40:12.012 --> 40:14.005
Then what are you
waiting for?

40:14.007 --> 40:15.019
I had to refuel
the lander.

40:15.021 --> 40:18.023
But, Mother, wait!

40:19.001 --> 40:21.007
Mother. Wait.

40:24.010 --> 40:26.011
Looks like Paul split off
from the group.

40:26.013 --> 40:28.016
I'll go after him.
You retrieve the others.

40:28.018 --> 40:30.013
I was using the carbos
to fuel the lander.

40:30.015 --> 40:32.001
It won't take
the carbos?

40:32.003 --> 40:35.022
It will take them,
but I need you to listen to me.

40:36.000 --> 40:37.014
We tested the carbos,

40:37.016 --> 40:41.001
but we never tested the pits
inside them.

40:41.003 --> 40:44.004
They're radioactive,
Mother.

40:44.006 --> 40:46.022
And it appears as soon
as the carbos are picked,

40:47.000 --> 40:48.012
the pits begin to decay,

40:48.014 --> 40:51.014
contaminating the rest
of the tubor.

40:51.016 --> 40:53.007
The Gen-1s were exposed
early enough

40:53.009 --> 40:55.016
that they must have developed
some resistance,

40:55.018 --> 40:57.021
which is likely why it took them
so much longer

40:57.023 --> 41:01.013
to...succumb
to the radiation's effects.

41:03.022 --> 41:07.002
You see, Mother,

41:07.004 --> 41:09.004
it wasn't you.

41:12.018 --> 41:14.021
You are a good parent.

41:14.023 --> 41:22.009
♪♪

41:22.011 --> 41:24.006
Omnibiotics.

41:24.008 --> 41:27.007
Give them to the children
as soon as you find them.

41:27.009 --> 41:30.011
They'll help counteract
the effects of the radiation.

41:31.022 --> 41:35.020
Thank you, Father,
for trusting in me.

41:35.022 --> 41:44.006
♪♪

41:44.008 --> 41:52.014
♪♪

41:52.016 --> 41:54.001
Holly: We lost Paul.

41:54.003 --> 41:55.002
It's our fault.

41:55.004 --> 41:56.014
We lost him.

41:58.016 --> 42:01.020
Do you have any more
of that stuff you gave us?

42:01.022 --> 42:03.000
Is it the baby?

42:03.002 --> 42:04.004
I don't know.

42:04.006 --> 42:06.002
It's been hurting
since yesterday.

42:06.004 --> 42:08.004
I didn't want to say anything
because I was afraid

42:08.006 --> 42:11.023
of upsetting
your...android.

42:12.001 --> 42:16.002
Do you really think
she's poisoning us?

42:16.004 --> 42:17.018
I don't know
that she's not.

42:17.020 --> 42:19.007
But she seemed so upset,

42:19.009 --> 42:21.023
like she was really worried
about me.

42:22.001 --> 42:25.007
I've never seen an android
behave that way before.

42:25.009 --> 42:27.019
[ Roaring sound in distance ]

42:27.021 --> 42:29.010
What is that?

42:30.021 --> 42:33.019
Vita: I told you.
I told you they weren't lying.

42:33.021 --> 42:36.001
There are things alive
out there.

42:36.003 --> 42:38.019
No one ever believes me
because I'm small,

42:38.021 --> 42:39.020
but I was right.

42:39.022 --> 42:41.021
Shut up.
They'll hear us.

42:41.023 --> 42:45.003
[ Roaring continues ]

42:47.009 --> 42:49.011
[ Creature grumbles ]

42:49.013 --> 42:52.009
Together: I wear the Armor
of Mithras and the Light.

42:52.011 --> 42:55.000
I am shielded
from all that is harmful.

42:55.002 --> 42:57.020
I wear the Armor of Mithras
and the Light.

42:57.022 --> 43:00.004
I am shielded
from all that is harmful.

43:00.006 --> 43:02.020
I wear the Armor of Mithras
and the Light.

43:02.022 --> 43:04.019
I am shielded
from all that is harmful.

43:04.021 --> 43:08.000
[ Creature hisses, squeals ]

43:08.002 --> 43:10.005
[ Grunts ]

43:10.007 --> 43:12.010
I wear the Armor of Mithras
and the Light.

43:12.012 --> 43:14.012
Campion: I am shielded
from all that is harmful.

43:14.014 --> 43:16.007
I wear the Armor of Mithras
and the Light.

43:16.009 --> 43:19.007
Have you managed to find
that pesky mouse yet, Campion?

43:19.009 --> 43:28.002
♪♪

43:28.004 --> 43:36.021
♪♪

43:36.023 --> 43:45.013
♪♪

43:45.015 --> 43:48.022
It's not Mother
that's making them sick.

43:49.000 --> 43:51.009
If you require proof,

43:51.011 --> 43:52.020
and I'm sure you do,

43:52.022 --> 43:56.018
load one of the carbos
into the bio-fuel tank.

43:56.020 --> 43:59.000
See for yourself.

43:59.002 --> 44:07.017
♪♪

44:07.019 --> 44:16.009
♪♪

44:16.011 --> 44:25.004
♪♪

44:25.006 --> 44:33.020
♪♪

44:33.022 --> 44:36.017
[ Machinery powering up ]

44:36.019 --> 44:44.010
♪♪

44:44.012 --> 44:46.014
[ Pinging ]

44:46.016 --> 44:48.013
♪♪

44:48.015 --> 44:50.007
Sorry, Mother.

44:52.003 --> 44:53.018
[ Grumbling noise ]

44:54.009 --> 44:58.022
♪♪

44:59.000 --> 45:01.010
Father!

45:01.012 --> 45:03.006
Father!

45:03.008 --> 45:05.003
[ Creature snarling ]

45:05.005 --> 45:09.006
♪♪

45:09.008 --> 45:10.017
Father.

45:10.019 --> 45:13.007
♪♪

45:13.009 --> 45:15.019
Father:
Open the door, Campion!

45:15.021 --> 45:22.006
♪♪

45:22.008 --> 45:24.014
It's tied up.
It can't escape.

45:24.016 --> 45:27.011
[ Wood pounding ]

45:27.013 --> 45:31.003
♪♪

45:31.005 --> 45:32.018
Did it hurt you?

45:35.003 --> 45:36.017
Your neck.

45:36.019 --> 45:38.018
It's nothing.

45:38.020 --> 45:40.003
Everything's alright.

45:40.005 --> 45:42.016
Go back to your beds.

45:42.018 --> 45:44.006
Go.

45:44.008 --> 45:48.003
♪♪

45:48.005 --> 45:50.005
[ Creature snarls ]

45:51.020 --> 45:54.016
I'm sorry, Father.

45:54.018 --> 45:57.013
You betrayed my trust,

45:57.015 --> 46:01.008
made me
look like a fool.

46:01.010 --> 46:06.000
If I cannot adequately care
for you and the other children,

46:06.002 --> 46:09.014
I am of no use
to the family.

46:09.016 --> 46:11.004
I need to be of use.

46:11.006 --> 46:13.016
Do you understand?

46:13.018 --> 46:15.017
You are useful.

46:15.019 --> 46:17.013
You saved us.

46:17.015 --> 46:19.018
I'll tell her
you saved us.

46:19.020 --> 46:22.004
Get back inside
with the others.

46:22.006 --> 46:28.023
♪♪

46:29.001 --> 46:35.015
♪♪

46:35.017 --> 46:39.013
Mother: Paul,
there's no need to run.

46:39.015 --> 46:40.021
If you can hear me,

46:40.023 --> 46:45.005
I want you to scream out
as loud as you can.

46:45.007 --> 46:47.010
You are not safe.

46:47.012 --> 46:49.005
♪♪

46:49.007 --> 46:50.011
Hunter?

46:50.013 --> 46:52.005
[ Coughs ]

46:52.007 --> 46:53.018
Tempest?

46:53.020 --> 46:55.017
Anybody, please!

46:55.019 --> 46:57.014
[ Coughs ]

46:57.016 --> 47:01.013
♪♪

47:01.015 --> 47:03.004
[ Twig snaps ]

47:04.021 --> 47:05.022
Who is that?

47:06.000 --> 47:07.004
[ Child giggles ]

47:07.006 --> 47:08.013
Vita, is that you?

47:08.015 --> 47:10.001
[ Singing playfully ]

47:10.003 --> 47:12.011
Wait.

47:12.013 --> 47:13.017
[ Coughs ]

47:13.019 --> 47:15.022
[ Singing continues ]
Wait.

47:16.000 --> 47:17.022
[ Coughs ]

47:18.000 --> 47:19.003
Wait.

47:19.005 --> 47:24.003
♪♪

47:24.005 --> 47:25.018
[ Coughs ]

47:25.020 --> 47:27.016
[ Singing fades ]

47:27.018 --> 47:29.008
I can't see you.

47:29.010 --> 47:31.011
[ Screams ]

47:31.013 --> 47:33.006
♪♪

47:33.008 --> 47:35.020
[ Coughs ]

47:35.022 --> 47:38.019
Campion! Anybody!

47:38.021 --> 47:47.021
♪♪

47:47.023 --> 47:56.022
♪♪

47:57.000 --> 48:05.023
♪♪

48:06.001 --> 48:15.002
♪♪

